Tokyo Electric’s Fuel Oil Use Rises 15 Percent in February

-- B y   Y u j i   O k a d a
-- 
2011-03-09T08:49:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-09/tokyo-electric-s-fuel-oil-use-rises-15-percent-in-february.html
Tokyo Electric Power Co. used 15
percent more  fuel oil  in February from a year earlier.  The utility consumed 222,000 kiloliters of fuel oil at its
thermal  power plants  in the month, up from 193,000 kiloliters in
February 2010, it said on its  website  today.  The following table shows Tokyo Electric’s consumption and
intakes of fuel oil, crude oil, liquefied natural gas and coal
for February. For fuel oil and crude, the volume is in
kiloliters while LNG and coal are in metric tons.  Source: Tokyo Electric Power Co.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Yuji Okada in Tokyo at 
